# {{PROJECT}}-web

Public-facing Next.js web app for {{PROJECT_DESCRIPTION}}.

## Stack

- Next.js 15 (App Router) + React 19
- TypeScript strict
- Tailwind CSS
- TanStack Query for server state
- NextAuth (Auth.js v5) — Google sign-in exchanged with `user-service`; the
  resulting bearer is forwarded to backend calls. JWT validation lives in
  `user-service` / `{{PROJECT}}-core`, **never** in this app.

## Quick start

```bash
npm install
cp .env.example .env.local
npm run dev
```

The dev server listens on `http://localhost:3080`. When running through
`docker-compose.yml` in `{{PROJECT}}-deployment/dev`, it is published on
`http://localhost:3080` (port mapped from the container's `:3000`). The
backend (fronted by nginx) is reachable inside the docker network at
`http://nginx/api`.

## Scripts

| Command            | What it does                          |
| ------------------ | ------------------------------------- |
| `npm run dev`      | Start the Next.js dev server (`:3080`) |
| `npm run build`    | Production build (standalone output)  |
| `npm run start`    | Run the production server             |
| `npm run lint`     | ESLint via `next lint`                |
| `npm run typecheck`| `tsc --noEmit`                        |
| `npm test`         | Vitest (jsdom) one-shot               |
| `npm run test:watch` | Vitest watch mode                   |
